<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="580" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1549,2008]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1549,1575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This species differs from all other known 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fletcher" authorityYear="2000" box="[738,834,1550,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mayawa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[738,834,1550,1575]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">Mayawa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in having a pair of large maculae on the crown and the paired processes on the aedeagus greatly reduced and inconspicuous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="581" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1549,2008]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,465]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="581" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1621,1647]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">Description</emphasis>
. Length of male 
<quantity box="[545,637,1621,1648]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
, female 
<quantity box="[739,832,1621,1648]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" unit="mm" value="3.8">3.8 mm</quantity>
. Overall color stramineous, head with pair of black maculae extended from between ocelli onto anterior half of crown, face (
<figureCitation box="[962,1047,1657,1683]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,385,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-104@5.[151,1436,380,1203]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mayawa bimaculata sp. nov., male holotype. A-B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E, genital capsule, lateral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, posteroventral view; H, aedeagus, lateral view. I–M, female paratype: I, abdominal sternite VII; J, first valvula; K, detail of same; L, second valvulae; M, detail of same." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556773" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556773/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
) unmarked except muscle scars on frontoclypeus slightly darker than adjacent parts; pronotum light grey posteromedialy; mesonotal triangles bright orange; forewing membrane light brown contrasting with pale stramineous wing veins; abdominal tergites brown, ovipositor blackCrown (
<figureCitation box="[428,516,1765,1791]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,385,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-104@5.[151,1436,380,1203]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mayawa bimaculata sp. nov., male holotype. A-B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E, genital capsule, lateral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, posteroventral view; H, aedeagus, lateral view. I–M, female paratype: I, abdominal sternite VII; J, first valvula; K, detail of same; L, second valvulae; M, detail of same." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556773" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556773/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
) produced anteriorly at obtuse angle, slightly longer medially than next to eyes. Forewing with second apical cell petiolate basally.Male pygofer lobe (
<figureCitation box="[950,1035,1801,1827]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,385,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-104@5.[151,1436,380,1203]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mayawa bimaculata sp. nov., male holotype. A-B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E, genital capsule, lateral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, posteroventral view; H, aedeagus, lateral view. I–M, female paratype: I, abdominal sternite VII; J, first valvula; K, detail of same; L, second valvulae; M, detail of same." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556773" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556773/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
) narrowly rounded distally, margin unmodified. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[497,582,1837,1863]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,385,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-104@5.[151,1436,380,1203]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mayawa bimaculata sp. nov., male holotype. A-B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E, genital capsule, lateral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, posteroventral view; H, aedeagus, lateral view. I–M, female paratype: I, abdominal sternite VII; J, first valvula; K, detail of same; L, second valvulae; M, detail of same." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556773" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556773/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
) approximately twice as long as wide, lateral margin weakly convex, with 5–6 macrosetae, apex obliquely rounded. Style preapical lobe acutely produced, apophysis narrow, elongate, evenly curved laterad, nearly parallel-sided, with five blunt, evenly spaced preapical teeth, apex bluntly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1423,1909,1935]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,385,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-104@5.[151,1436,380,1203]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mayawa bimaculata sp. nov., male holotype. A-B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E, genital capsule, lateral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, posteroventral view; H, aedeagus, lateral view. I–M, female paratype: I, abdominal sternite VII; J, first valvula; K, detail of same; L, second valvulae; M, detail of same." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556773" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556773/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with dorsal apodeme approximately parallel to shaft in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1038,1128,1945,1971]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,385,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-104@5.[151,1436,380,1203]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mayawa bimaculata sp. nov., male holotype. A-B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E, genital capsule, lateral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, posteroventral view; H, aedeagus, lateral view. I–M, female paratype: I, abdominal sternite VII; J, first valvula; K, detail of same; L, second valvulae; M, detail of same." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556773" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556773/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">Fig. 3H</figureCitation>
), shaft evenly tapered from base to apex, slightly sinuate in lateral view; in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[848,936,1981,2007]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,385,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-104@5.[151,1436,380,1203]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mayawa bimaculata sp. nov., male holotype. A-B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E, genital capsule, lateral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, posteroventral view; H, aedeagus, lateral view. I–M, female paratype: I, abdominal sternite VII; J, first valvula; K, detail of same; L, second valvulae; M, detail of same." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556773" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556773/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
) shaft parallel-sided with pair of very short, inconspicuous retrorse lateral spines near midlength and pair of small lateral teeth near apex, apex rounded; gonopore relatively short, ovoid, situated near apex. Female sternite VII posterior margin trilobed medially with medial lobe shorter and narrower than lateral lobes (
<figureCitation box="[651,729,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,385,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-104@5.[151,1436,380,1203]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mayawa bimaculata sp. nov., male holotype. A-B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E, genital capsule, lateral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, posteroventral view; H, aedeagus, lateral view. I–M, female paratype: I, abdominal sternite VII; J, first valvula; K, detail of same; L, second valvulae; M, detail of same." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556773" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556773/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Fig. 3I</figureCitation>
). First valvula dorsal sculpture squamiform, merging with ventral sculpture near apex (
<figureCitation box="[430,500,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,385,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-104@5.[151,1436,380,1203]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mayawa bimaculata sp. nov., male holotype. A-B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E, genital capsule, lateral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, posteroventral view; H, aedeagus, lateral view. I–M, female paratype: I, abdominal sternite VII; J, first valvula; K, detail of same; L, second valvulae; M, detail of same." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556773" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556773/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Figs 3</figureCitation>
J–K). Second valvulae with median dorsal tooth moderately prominent, distal teeth irregular (
<figureCitation box="[262,331,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,385,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-104@5.[151,1436,380,1203]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mayawa bimaculata sp. nov., male holotype. A-B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E, genital capsule, lateral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, posteroventral view; H, aedeagus, lateral view. I–M, female paratype: I, abdominal sternite VII; J, first valvula; K, detail of same; L, second valvulae; M, detail of same." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556773" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556773/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Figs 3</figureCitation>
L–M).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1324,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,465]" box="[199,1324,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
